gic [1:0] pht [127:0]`.\n   - GHR: `logic [6:0] ghr`.\n   - Index calculation: `pc ^ ghr`.\n   - Counter saturation: 00 <-> 01 <-> 10 <-> 11.\n\n5. **Advice to avoid syntax errors**:\n   - Ensure all indices are within bounds (7-bit XOR with 7-bit PC results in 7-bit index, which is 0-127, perfect for 128 entries).\n   - Use `always @(*)` for combinational logic.\n   - Use `always @(posedge clk)` for sequential logic.\n   - Handle `areset` as asynchronous active-high as requested (though the spec says 'Reset is asynchronous active-high', the interface says `areset` and the testbench uses it. I will implement it as asynchronous).\n   - Careful with bit widths: PC and History are 7 bits. PHT index is 7 bits (0-127).",
